fields.name: Luxury End Grain Multi-wood Chopping Board
fields.description: Exquisite individual wooden piece luxury end grain  chopping board. Produced from Acacia, Sapele, Hard Maple, Maple,  Ash & Oak. Thick, durable and kinder to knife blades

fields.name: Round Wooden Chopping Board
fields.description: Provide a perfect cutting surface with this round wooden chopping board. Constructed from multiple blocks of wood that are glued and pressed together, the board is incredibly robust and will not warp over time, saving you money on replacements. Its premium wooden construction also means knives will not blunt when used on it, making it easier for you to keep them in great condition. Featuring finger grooves, the board is also easy to lift to allow for easy placement and cleaning. We would recommend that this board is hand washed and dried thoroughly before storing.

fields.name: Kombi Bamboo and Plastic Chopping Board
fields.description: This makes barbecuing, cooking and baking a lot more fun. Unsightly scratches on your worktop are a thing of the past with this chopping board. Features a juice gutter for catching liquid - suitable for steaks, roasts and other juicy foods. Food-safe, non-slip surface. Bamboo is environmentally-friendly, renewable, knife-friendly and durable.

fields.name: Plastic Chopping Board 18x12 Inch White
fields.description: Easy to clean plastic chopping board, ideal for food preparation, durable chopping board.

fields.name: Victorinox Fibrox Chef Knife 12.5cm
fields.description: With over 100 years of experience in making the finest knives, Victorinox have become world-renowned for the quality of their products. The 5" chef knife from Victorinox is expertly-crafted to provide professional results with each slice. The high-carbon stainless steel provides an ultra-sharp edge that cuts through the toughest of produce with ease, whilst also being highly durable and easy to maintain.

fields.name: homgeek Professional Kitchen Knife Set with Wooden Block

Knife Sharpener—Keeping in excellent condition will enhance chef capabilities. Kitchen Scissors—Cleaning skin off of poultry and trimming fat meat.

fields.name: My Kitchen Silicone-Coated Cooking Spatula
fields.description:
Perfect for stirring, stir-frying and getting right into the corners of pans to get out every last scrap, our My Kitchen Large Silicone Spatula is one of the utensils you’ll always find yourself reaching for.

In one of four kitchen-cheering colours – pastel blue, pale green, coral pink or purple – it’s made of stain-resistant, odour-resistant, heat-resistant silicone so it won’t damage your prized non-stick pans. The flexible edges help you get right into any corners if you’re using it for scraping out pans. There’s a handy hanging hole in the handle and it has a stainless steel core for extra strength.

Dishwasher safe for easy cleaning.

Heat-resistant to 230°C.

fields.name: Wusthof Gourmet Slotted Spatula
fields.description: This offset slotted spatula, or fish turner features a thin, flexible blade designed to slide and flip delicate foods with ease. Just right for cradling delicate fish or letting grease drip away from burgers. This versatile tool made by renowned German knife company Wusthof has instantly become a chef favourite. Dishwasher safe

Set contains: slotted spoon, solid spoon, slotted turner, solid turner and risotto spoon.
Crafted from environmentally friendly bamboo - ideal for use on non stick surfaces. Each piece has a hanging hook for practical storage.

fields.name: Eco 3 Piece Non-Stick Saucepan Set
fields.description:
This scratch proof, non-stick pan set is ideal for easy cooking. With a soft grip and stay cool handle this pan has perfect heat distribution for energy efficient cooking. This pan set is oven safe up to 150°C/300°F/Gas Mark 2. Palm oil free and PFOA free. Better for you and our planet.

Made from recycled materials and recyclable too, including the packaging.

Able to be used with metal utensils this pan is suitable for all direct heat sources including induction. fields.name: Non-Stick Flexible Muffin Pan
fields.description:
This flexible silicone six hole pan is perfect for making muffins, cupcakes and Yorkshire puddings. Silicone is non-stick and totally flexible for easy release and turning out of cakes as well as tolerating temperatures exceeding most ovens the pan does not absorb odours and will not distort or taint, so is totally reusable time and time again. Featuring a matt black exterior the pan also cooks the contents evenly and a little quicker. Oven safe to 250°C (482°F)

What is Lorem Ipsum?
Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.

Why do we use it?
It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal distribution of letters, as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like readable English. Many desktop publishing packages and web page editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for 'lorem ipsum' will uncover many web sites still in their infancy. Various versions have evolved over the years, sometimes by accident, sometimes on purpose (injected humour and the like).


Where does it come from?
Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of "de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum" (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..", comes from a line in section 1.10.32.
